Update WebGL build on GitHub Pages (Terminal)
1) Go to the repo
cd "/Users/Moses/Desktop/My Writing Career/Code Projects/Games/BlacksmithBlues"
2) Pull latest from GitHub first (prevents “fetch first” rejection)
git pull --rebase origin main
3) Replace the docs/ folder with your newest WebGL build

(Replace BlacksmithBluesTest4 with whatever your latest build folder name is.)

rm -rf docs
mkdir -p docs
cp -R "BuildWebGL/BlacksmithBluesTest4/Build" docs/
cp -R "BuildWebGL/BlacksmithBluesTest4/TemplateData" docs/
cp "BuildWebGL/BlacksmithBluesTest4/index.html" docs/
4) Stage, commit, push
git add -A docs
git commit -m "Update WebGL build"
git push origin main
Quick verification (optional but useful)
git log -1 --oneline

And on the live site, if it looks unchanged:

Hard refresh: Cmd + Shift + R

Or open in an incognito window (Unity WebGL caches aggressively)

If you ever see the “fetch first” error again

Just run:

git pull --rebase origin main
git push origin main
